01/04/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Finnish President Tarja Halonen voiced her country's support on Thursday (March 31st) for Serbia's EU bid.
She stressed that there is no shortcut to membership and the country should meet all criteria.
President Boris Tadic thanked Halonen for the support and voiced optimism that Serbia will be given EU candidate status by the end of the year.
He reiterated that Serbia is willing to complete its co-operation with the Hague war crimes tribunal.
(Tanjug, RTS, B92 - 31/03/11)
